WEBVTT

00:01.922 --> 00:04.120
<i>That happygolucky looking kid is me.</i>

00:04.122 --> 00:07.254
<i>I was the smartest person
I had ever met,</i>

00:07.256 --> 00:10.121
<i>and I was convinced I would
grow up to be an astronaut</i>

00:10.123 --> 00:12.988
<i>and the first man on Saturn.</i>

00:12.990 --> 00:15.754
<i>This is me the summer
after my first year in college.</i>

00:15.756 --> 00:18.055
<i>I was on my first car, third girlfriend,</i>

00:18.057 --> 00:20.889
<i>and second fake ID.
I had come to the conclusion</i>

00:20.891 --> 00:23.222
<i>that space travel
probably wasn't in my future</i>

00:23.224 --> 00:26.989
<i>and that psychology
was for losers and weaklings.</i>

00:26.991 --> 00:29.256
<i>You can figure out what this is.</i>

00:29.258 --> 00:32.423
<i>The point being we move through
our lives shedding skins,</i>

00:32.424 --> 00:35.623
<i>kissing older versions
of ourselves goodbye</i>

00:35.625 --> 00:37.690
<i>and new ones hello.</i>

00:41.225 --> 00:42.557
Bull?

00:42.559 --> 00:44.590
Mind if I join you for your 9:00?

00:44.592 --> 00:46.158
What 9:00?

00:46.160 --> 00:47.657
Wh... That bigdeal attorney
from upstate

00:47.659 --> 00:50.091
that you told me to fit into
your schedule this morning.

00:50.093 --> 00:51.391
What are you talking about?

00:51.393 --> 00:52.625
Were you drinking last night?

00:52.627 --> 00:54.324
Was it a day that ends in "Y"?

00:54.326 --> 00:55.858
You don't remember me calling you.

00:55.860 --> 00:57.324
Calling me what?

00:57.853 --> 00:59.259
I smell a setup.

01:00.420 --> 01:02.526
Do you want me to walk in first?

01:02.528 --> 01:04.045
I'd love that.

01:06.661 --> 01:08.893
Mr. Burnam?

01:08.895 --> 01:10.626
So sorry to have kept you waiting.

01:10.628 --> 01:12.626
Dr. Bull just arrived.

01:15.162 --> 01:17.727
Mr. Burnam?

01:17.729 --> 01:20.527
Dr. Bull. Thank you so much
for seeing me.

01:20.529 --> 01:24.161
You're a big deal attorney?

01:25.063 --> 01:27.927
II... am an attorney.

01:28.929 --> 01:30.695
How old are you?

01:30.697 --> 01:33.228
24. 25 in March.

01:33.230 --> 01:34.961
I get this all the time.

01:34.963 --> 01:36.256
Okay.

01:36.830 --> 01:39.095
I'm gonna walk around my desk here

01:39.097 --> 01:40.729
and put myself in that chair and hope

01:40.731 --> 01:43.462
that in the time it takes me
to walk from here to there,

01:43.464 --> 01:45.929
I start to remember who you are
and why you're here.

